{"page":1,"results":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":4415,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Federico Fellini","original_name":"Federico Fellini","popularity":1.2094,"profile_path":"/r0GTpMWUrxgPRbMmv38mNggOBvA.jpg","known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/y2FNZLHynsevBnVTocGW6c3pQpr.jpg","id":422,"title":"8½","original_title":"8½","overview":"Guido Anselmi, a film director, finds himself creatively barren at the peak of his career. Urged by his doctors to rest, Anselmi heads for a luxurious resort, but a sorry group gathers—his producer, staff, actors, wife, mistress, and relatives—each one begging him to get on with the show. In retreat from their dependency, he fantasizes about past women and dreams of his childhood.","poster_path":"/23VIf7zNxAgaXwIlvzd3IvOd9sY.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"it","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":4.011,"release_date":"1963-02-14","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":8.096,"vote_count":2523},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/eN2NdMeJLNzLYzWIEEoaGzZAsiD.jpg","id":439,"title":"La Dolce Vita","original_title":"La dolce vita","overview":"Episodic journey of journalist Marcello who struggles to find his place in the world, torn between the allure of Rome's elite social scene and the stifling domesticity offered by his girlfriend, all the while searching for a way to become a serious writer.","poster_path":"/dZ2v0DAX4aCZartCzZdg4ZinSW2.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"it","genre_ids":[35,18],"popularity":3.6167,"release_date":"1960-02-05","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":8.034,"vote_count":2029},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/iFQzlUmO5QmMPcSHHDdfd522x33.jpg","id":7857,"title":"Amarcord","original_title":"Amarcord","overview":"In an Italian seaside town, young Titta gets into trouble with his friends and watches various local eccentrics as they engage in often absurd behavior. Frequently clashing with his stern father and defended by his doting mother, Titta witnesses the action